# Copy this file to .dev.vars for local development.
# Values here are only used by `wrangler pages dev` and are never committed.
# D1 and KV bindings (DB, KV) are wired automatically via wrangler.jsonc —
# no entries are needed here for those bindings.
#
# Add any secret environment variables below:
# MY_SECRET=replace_me
#
# Google Gemini API key — used by the /api/gemini server-side proxy function.
# The key is stored as a Cloudflare secret (GRMINI_API_KEY) and is never
# exposed to the client. Obtain a key from https://aistudio.google.com/
# GRMINI_API_KEY=replace_me

# ─── Storage adapter selector ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Controls which StorageAdapter is used for the tenants / brand-profiles /
# visits / scan-captures collections (src/lib/storage/adapterFactory.ts).
#
# 'local'  (default) — browser localStorage / sessionStorage; no change to
#           existing behaviour.  Safe for all local development.
# 'd1'     — Cloudflare D1 adapter (src/lib/storage/d1Adapter.ts).  Requires
#           the ATLAS_REPORTS_D1 binding to be present in the runtime context.
#           Only activate when running `wrangler pages dev` against a real or
#           local D1 database that has migrations 0013–0016 applied.
#
# VITE_STORAGE_ADAPTER=local
